snippet.title: SUNS at WARRIORS | FULL GAME HIGHLIGHTS | October 24, 2023
snippet.description:
Never miss a moment with the latest news, trending stories and highlights to bring you closer to your favorite players and teams.
Download now: https://app.link.nba.com/NBAapp

The Phoenix Suns defeat the Golden State Warriors, 108-104, and improve to 1-0 on the season. Devin Booker led the Suns with 32 points, 8 assists, and 6 rebounds as Kevin Durant (18 points, 10 rebounds) and Jusuf Nurkic (14 points, 14 rebounds) totaled 32 points. Stephen Curry led the Warriors with 27 points and 5 rebounds while Klay Thompson (15 points, 7 rebounds) and Chris Paul (14 points, 9 assists, 6 rebounds) combined for 29 points. The Warriors are now 0-1 on the year.
